
Node.js -> runs Javascript on a server (Runtime, runs your code)
Express -> Framework for Node.js (set of tools + rules that help you structure & build an app)

What I did so far:
- ran "npm init -y" (backend folder is now a Node project)
- ran "npm install express" (installs the framework that lets us build routes like /auth/login)
- ran "npm install -D nodemon" (automatically restarts your servwer when you change code, saves a 	ton of time)
- mkdir srcs, touch server.js

To run, do:
- npm run dev





